# LSPosed Module Security Audit Skill

Systematic security review framework for Android LSPosed/Xposed modules, distilled from the KunYuShu (坤舆枢) full-stack audit covering 493 files across 14 review dimensions. Covers Java/Kotlin layer, native C/C++ layer, IPC boundary, anti-detection, build config, and runtime hardening.

## Severity Framework

| Level | Definition | Response |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| CRITICAL | System crash (SIGSEGV/ANR/soft-reboot), data breach, code injection | Must fix immediately |
| HIGH | Probable runtime exception, state corruption, anti-detection bypass | Should fix promptly |
| MEDIUM | Conditional race, specific scenario reproducible | Should fix |
| LOW | Theoretical risk, hardening opportunity | Optional |
| INFO | Documented acceptable risk | Track only |

