## Checklist 1: ContentProvider / IPC Security

### 1.1 Provider Authentication
- [ ] `query()` has `Binder.getCallingUid()` check (NOT only `insert()`/`update()`)
- [ ] `enforceAllowedReader()` validates against `SYSTEM_UID` or self-UID
- [ ] Manifest declares `android:permission` with `signature` level
- [ ] Manifest sets `android:grantUriPermissions="false"`
- [ ] No bypass via `call()` method

### 1.2 IPC Encryption (if custom command channel)
- [ ] Session key uses `SecureRandom` (256-bit minimum)
- [ ] AES-CTR with random IV per field (never reuse IV)
- [ ] HMAC-SHA256 signature covering commandId + nonce + timestamp + sequence
- [ ] Constant-time HMAC comparison (`constantTimeEquals`, not `!=`)
- [ ] Replay protection: 30s time window + nonce dedup (512-2048 entry LRU)
- [ ] Outer session key comparison also constant-time (not short-circuit `!=`)
- [ ] `exchange_key` uses UID check via `BinderUtils.isManagerApp()`
- [ ] Each command wrapped in `runCatching` for atomicity

### 1.3 Payload Validation
- [ ] Array/bundle size caps (e.g., `count <= 500`) to prevent OOM DoS
- [ ] Nonce cache has upper bound (FIFO eviction after N entries)
- [ ] Sequence number monotonic check
- [ ] Timestamp within valid window

