## Checklist 3: Concurrency & Thread Safety

### 3.1 Shared Mutable State (Kotlin/Java)
- [ ] All multi-thread-accessed `var` fields use `@Volatile`
- [ ] God objects (60+ var fields in one singleton) identified and flagged
- [ ] `HashMap` used in multi-thread context → `ConcurrentHashMap`
- [ ] Counter fields use `AtomicInteger`, not bare `Int`
- [ ] Check-then-act patterns protected by lock or atomic CAS
- [ ] `forceDisable` guard pattern: volatile write before enable toggle

### 3.2 Coroutine Safety
- [ ] NO `GlobalScope` in ViewModel (use `viewModelScope` or lifecycle-aware scope)
- [ ] `isPaused` flags are `@Volatile` or `AtomicBoolean` (channel happens-before insufficient for external readers)
- [ ] `while (channel.receive() != Resume)` has timeout break (5s) to prevent permanent hang
- [ ] Pause/resume controllers genericized (not duplicated in `CoroutineController` + `CoroutineRouteMock`)

### 3.3 Native Concurrency (C/C++)
- [ ] `OBFUSCATE` macro static init uses `std::atomic<bool>` or `std::once_flag`
- [ ] `initLinearMap()` lazy init uses `std::call_once` or mutex
- [ ] Global char buffers (`g_app_cache_dir`) have proper memory ordering
- [ ] Shared memory struct copies are atomic or use seqlock pattern
- [ ] `thread_local` recursion guards for hook callbacks

