## Checklist 4: Native C/C++ Code Safety

### 4.1 Dobby Inline Hook Safety
- [ ] ALL `DobbyHook` return values checked (non-zero → orig = nullptr)
- [ ] ALL `orig_*` function pointers null-checked before call (syscall fallback on null)
- [ ] Constructor hooks gated by `is_system_server_process()` check
- [ ] `install_hooks()` uses `std::atomic_bool` re-entrance guard
- [ ] Hook installation wrapped in `safe_execute_failfast` (G3) or `safe_execute_with_watchdog` (G4/G5)

### 4.2 ELF/Memory Parsing
- [ ] `e_shnum` upper bound check before for-loop (prevent OOB read on corrupted ELF)
- [ ] `sh_offset` validated within `[0, mmap_size)` before `offsetOf<T>()`
- [ ] `std::stol` replaced with `strtoull` (no exception → `std::terminate`)
- [ ] `initModuleBase` has try/catch or uses non-throwing parse
- [ ] `PT_LOAD` range detection iterates ALL segments (max `end`), not `break` on first

### 4.3 Signal Safety
- [ ] `crash_recovery_handler`: only async-signal-safe functions (`write`, `open`, `close`, `siglongjmp`)
- [ ] NO `malloc`, `printf`, `mutex_lock` in signal handler
- [ ] Code ranges (`is_our_address()`) initialized BEFORE `sigaction` install
- [ ] Watchdog `pthread_detach` path: worker must NOT hold ART locks or JNI env
- [ ] `CRASH_RECOVERY_END` recovered-flag checked correctly (not `active` which is always reset)

### 4.4 Page Size Compatibility
- [ ] `-Wl,-z,max-page-size=16384` in CMakeLists.txt for 16KB page devices (Android 15+)
- [ ] Dobby POSIX patch path uses dynamic `sysconf(_SC_PAGESIZE)`
- [ ] Verify with `llvm-readelf -l` that `PT_LOAD Align` = 0x4000

