## Checklist 5: Code Quality & Architecture

### 5.1 God Object Detection
- [ ] Any `object` singleton with >20 `var` fields (flag as God Object)
- [ ] State proxy layers (direct getter/setter delegation) — eliminate or justify
- [ ] Any class >1000 lines (split by responsibility)

### 5.2 Kotlin Anti-Patterns
- [ ] Extension property abuse (>10 ext props on `Context` for SharedPreferences)
- [ ] Recursive retry → `while` loop
- [ ] `forEach { }` + lambda in hot path → `for (x in items)` 
- [ ] `runCatching` in dispatch loop → `try/catch`
- [ ] Commented-out code blocks >10 lines → delete
- [ ] Key name typos in SP (e.g., `Regitser` → `Register`)
- [ ] Dead imports / unused variable bindings

### 5.3 Reflection Usage
- [ ] Method references cached in `@Volatile` variables (not per-call `firstOrNull`)
- [ ] Constructor reflection cached (not `constructor.newInstance()` per GNSS cycle)
- [ ] `hookAllMethods` return value not discarded (use count-check variant instead)

### 5.4 Shell Command Safety
- [ ] `ShellUtils` validates command against whitelist (`ALLOWED_ROOT_COMMANDS`)
- [ ] No `rm`, `sh`, `echo`, `dd` in whitelist
- [ ] Parameters validated: non-empty, no NUL bytes, regex `[A-Za-z0-9._+-]+`
- [ ] Shell quoting via `quoteForRootShell()` (single-quote wrapping)
- [ ] Unused `setEnforceMode()` dead code removed

