## Checklist 6: Anti-Detection Hardening

### 6.1 String Obfuscation
- [ ] XOR key space >8 bits (current single-byte key = 256 brute-force)
- [ ] All filter markers obfuscated (not bare strings in `maps_filter.cpp`)
- [ ] Decrypted strings zeroed after use (not persistent in `_buf`)
- [ ] `OBFUSCATE` static init uses atomic guard (concurrency review item)

### 6.2 Backtrace & Maps Filtering
- [ ] `backtrace()` hooked AND `_Unwind_Backtrace` hooked (not deferred)
- [ ] `open`/`openat` maps filter active in RELEASE builds (not `#ifdef DEBUG` only)
- [ ] `/proc/self/exe`, `/proc/*/task/*/status`, `/sys/kernel/` paths covered
- [ ] `readlink /proc/self/fd/N` bypass addressed
- [ ] `memfd_create` FD redirection working for all maps variants
- [ ] JNI trampoline frames (`art_quick_generic_jni_trampoline`) filtered
- [ ] Region detection uses file-name pattern + ELF identifier (not just `strstr`)

### 6.3 Sensor Randomization Quality
- [ ] Per-sample noise added (not static values set once at startup)
- [ ] Gyroscope random walk drift simulated
- [ ] Step counter values consistent across `SensorEventQueueWrite` AND `ConvertToSensorEvent`
- [ ] Timestamp-value correlation preserved (not decoupled)
- [ ] PRNG reseeded per session, not using weak `rand()`

### 6.4 ArtMethod & Property Protection
- [ ] `cacheOriginalEntryPoints()` actually populates the cache (not no-op)
- [ ] Lookup key matches actual `Unsafe.getLong` semantics (offset, not method name)
- [ ] `getObject` counterpart hooked (not just `getLong`)
- [ ] `VarHandle` bypass (Android 14+) addressed
- [ ] Property masker covers all LSPosed-exposing keys
- [ ] `PackageManager` API filtering covers all 5 query methods

