## Checklist 7: Runtime Defense Layers

### 7.1 Java Exception Boundary (Layer 1)
- [ ] ALL `system_server` hooks individually wrapped in `runCatching`
- [ ] `handleLoadPackage` each hook init in separate try/catch
- [ ] `handleInstruction` command dispatch in outer `runCatching`
- [ ] Each `afterHook` method in WlanHook has per-method `runCatching`

### 7.2 DomainGuard (Crash Isolation)
- [ ] Per-domain sliding window crash counter (5/300s)
- [ ] Install crash loop detection (3/120s → safeMode)
- [ ] `safeMode` flag is `@Volatile`
- [ ] Counter uses `AtomicInteger`
- [ ] `checkInstallCrashLoop()` called at `handleLoadPackage` START

### 7.3 Native Crash Recovery (Layer 2)
- [ ] `CRASH_RECOVERY_BEGIN/END` macros used per hook function
- [ ] Recovery counter ≤3 per boot, then terminal despair
- [ ] Per-step disable marker written atomically on crash
- [ ] Signal handler forwards non-own crashes to original handler

### 7.4 Safety Gate Chain (Layer 3-4)
- [ ] DESPAIR_LOCK checked first (terminal lock blocks all)
- [ ] ART_VERSION_LOCK prevents ART manipulation after OTA
- [ ] VERSION_GATE whitelist check for risky ops
- [ ] BOOT_GATE safe-mode detection (`persist.sys.safemode`)
- [ ] PERSISTENT_DISABLE per-step marker prevents retry
- [ ] QEMU detection: 8-gate scoring + challenge token

### 7.5 FlightRecorder & Diagnostics
- [ ] Ring buffer (256 events) with bootstrap device identity
- [ ] Persistent JSONL flush
- [ ] CrashForensics with SHA256 fingerprint
- [ ] BBN-tagged logging (domain-tagged error routing)

